data.content: When did the second Trump administration impose an immediate freeze on research grants, communications, hiring, and meetings at the National Institutes of Health?

According to the provided text, the second Trump administration imposed an immediate freeze on scientific grants, communications, hiring, and meetings at the National Institutes of Health (NIH) on January 22, 2025.
How much of the institute's operations were affected by this decision?
$47.4 billion worth of activities at the National Institutes of Health (NIH) were affected.

The new moons of Saturn were discovered by astronomers using the Canada-France-Hawaii Telescope, and the number of new moons discovered was 128.
